<TEXT>
a state lawmakers 20yearold son was 
convicted friday of intentionally killing his mother with a bow and 
arrow as jurors rejected his claim the death was accidental 
chad goetsch who testified that the hunting arrow slipped when 
his mothers voice startled him showed no emotion when the verdict 
was read he is the adopted son of state rep robert goetsch who 
testified against him 
the jury deliberated 4 hours before finding goetsch guilty of 
firstdegree intentional homicide he was also found guilty of 
endangering safety for injuries suffered by his father in a 
struggle 
circuit judge daniel klossner scheduled sentencing for oct 29 
goetsch faces a mandatory life term for the intentional homicide 
conviction 
the second charge arose from allegations he aimed another arrow 
at his father and fought with him after shooting his 51yearold 
mother carolyn the arrow pierced his mothers heart 
the killing took place after goetsch arrived at the family home 
in oak grove early nov 8 from his college residence 
the elder goetsch had testified that his son had threatened the 
mother 
we talked about buying a gun he said she started 
insisting on locking the doors she said she was afraid of him she 
was afraid he was going to kill her 
the younger goetsch testified thursday that he never meant to 
release the arrow but his mother startled him 
my whole body jerked and contracted and i lost control of the 
bow string he said he denied that he aimed another arrow at his 
father 
defense attorney henry conti said previous family conflicts 
described during the trial perhaps had an effect in the incident 
that morning im afraid it poured over to the jurys decision 
he said the verdict would be appealed 
the elder goetsch who was present when the verdict was read 
said the trial ended as it should but the outcome brought no 
relief 
justice has triumphed in this case but i feel bad 
terrible said goetsch who adopted chad at age 4 after marrying 
the boys mother 
