<TEXT>
a model of a small nasa space taxi to 
shuttle crew and cargo between earth and an orbiting station was 
unveiled friday 
fiftyfive students from two universities designed the mockup 
of the spacecraft that would be launched by a titan 4 rocket and 
would land on a runway similar to space shuttle landings 
the national aeronautics and space administration has said it 
will use the model of the hl20 which has a 23foot wingspan and 
is 29 feet long space shuttles are more than four times as long 
and three times as wide 
the nose of the hl20 resembles space shuttles with a sleek 
sweptwing tail section 
the space taxi is being considered as a means of moving 
small loads of cargo and people to and from the planned space 
station freedom 
it was unveiled on the north carolina state university campus 
students from both nc state and north carolina aampt state 
university worked on the vehicle 
the agreement with nasa was that we would do the structural 
design and construct the working model said nc state aerospace 
engineering professor fred dejarnette they provided the external 
shape the computer geometry of the vehicle 
the university is home to the mars mission research center 
nasas goal is to reach mars by 2019 and scientists say a working 
space station would be needed to accomplish such a trip 
to aid in mars mission research the center has a budget of 84 
million from nasa over five years dejarnette is the centers 
director 
</TEXT>
