<TEXT>
a golfer reaching for a ball toppled 
150 feet off the edge of a cliff and survived with a broken rib and 
cuts 
bill sadler 45 a novice golfer had not played pebble beach 
before thursday when he took the plunge into sand near the eighth 
hole on one of the countrys most difficult courses 
im extremely lucky thursday the 13th wasnt an unlucky day 
after all sadler said friday from a hospital in nearby monterey 
the ball was just over the edge of the cliff i reached down 
trying to get it and the ground gave way he said 
sadler a lieutenant commander in the british royal navy has 
lived in nearby pacific grove for three years he is an 
oceanographer assigned to an annex of the navel postgraduate school 
in monterey 
an army helicopter airlifted him off the sand and onto the golf 
course he suffered only a broken rib and minor cuts 
he was lucky said sheriffs deputy ray george this 
should have been a coroners case 
asked if hed try golf again sadler replied well well see 
i know im not doing any more cliff walking 
