<TEXT>
three senior members of a 
whitesupremacist group have been convicted of more than 100 
offenses committed in an 18month terrorism campaign against 
asians 
a perth district court jury on friday found the men guilty of 
conspiring to drive asians out of western australia state with a 
series of tactics including arson attacks on perth chinese 
restaurants 
they also carried out a string of thefts to fund the movement 
which reportedly has offshoots in other states 
two defendants argued they were patriotic australians fighting 
for their country 
a former member of the group who had testified against the 
defendants received plastic surgery and was given a new identity 
overseas 
judge kevin hammond planned sentencing hearings on separate days 
next week 
