<TEXT>
sharon pratt dixon is a political unknown but 
the woman who is favored to become the next mayor of the nations 
capital is hardly a political novice 
the probable successor to marion barry dixon scored a stunning 
victory tuesday in the citys democratic primary her first bid for 
public office 
she didnt have the kind of money in the primary to put out 
those television commercials this is sharon pratt dixon and this 
is who i am said julius hobson a longtime observer of city 
politics 
but it would be a mistake to call her a political newcomer 
she doesnt have a real daytoday record but she does have a long 
involvement in local and national politics said hobson 
she was short on cash staff and supplies but dixons theme 
throughout the primary campaign was that the time had come to get 
rid of the bloated bureaucracy and inefficiency associated with 
barrys administration 
while her message had become familiar on election day voters in 
this city of 620000 still know little about the 46yearold 
divorced mother of two or the depth of her political experience 
a former treasurer of the democratic national committee dixon 
learned how to run a citywide campaign when she managed former 
carter aide patricia roberts harris unsuccessful effort to defeat 
barry in the districts 1982 primary 
and when she made her victory speech tuesday dnc chairman ron 
brown chose to stand by her side 
dixon is also an old friend of virginia gov douglas wilder who 
fashioned his own underdog campaign last year in becoming the old 
dominions first black governor 
if elected in november she would break new ground herself 
becoming the first black woman to serve as mayor of a major 
american city 
shes no stranger to congress which reviews the annual city 
budget and frequently takes a more critical look when things arent 
going well for the local government within hours of her victory 
she had set up a meeting with senate majority leader george 
mitchell dmaine 
the citys image on capitol hill badly tarnished by barrys 
drug conviction and the local governments 93 million deficit 
already seems to be regaining some of its luster 
im a very optimistic person and a very determined person 
dixon said wen asked to describe herself i dont take no for an 
answer very easily 
those who know the slight bespectacled woman agree 
shes always been a very aggressive person eager to prove 
herself said her aunt aimee pratt i remember when she was a 
little girl and she would be climbing on a chair or something i 
would tell her not to and she would say but i can i can 
her business resume is lengthy too an attorney she rose 
through the ranks at the potomac electric power co to become 
director of the utilitys consumer affairs department before 
launching her longshot mayoral campaign 
shes a very warm dynamic intelligent person said w reid 
thompson pepco board chairman she is very relaxed with people 
and she shows a lot of poise and charm 
shes really succeeded in the mainstream of politics and in 
the business world said eddie williams director of the joint 
center for political studies a blackoriented think tank shes 
a technician very good with numbers her background is more 
corporate than civil rights 
dixon has taught at the university of the district of columbias 
law school worked on a commission that took authority over the 
citys criminal code from congress and gave it to the city council 
and served in a variety of legal posts at pepco 
and while voters responded to dixons repeated sometimes 
strident calls for cuts in the city work force and elimination of 
other forms of cronyism those familiar with her believe there is 
another side to her 
something people dont see is that she is very gentle not 
aloof at all her aunt said you have to get to know her but 
once you do shes very approachable and warm 
it wasnt until after barry was convicted of a cocaine 
possession charge less than a month before the primary that 
city residents started paying attention to dixon she scored a 
major coup two weeks later when the washington post endorsed her 
over four rivals with longtime ties to city government 
democrats outnumber republicans here by a 9to1 margin so 
dixon appears headed for victory nov 6 against gop candidate 
maurice turner a former city police chief 
