entrenched enemy drew a parallel with the battle on the somme on 
july 1 1916 when there was enormous british bloodshed in just 
minutes 
that gives you the outside parameter of what kind of 
casualties can result from assaulting fortified positions head 
on he said you can go much lower but still it is probably 
the most difficult kind of warfare 
we need to remember that they iraqis fought the iraniraq war 
primarily on the defensive that is by far the strongest form of 
war it is not decisive but it can certainly cause enormous 
casualties 
added blackwell if theyre defending the city room by room to 
the death were back to islandclearing operations in the pacific 
in world war ii 
on the other hand the americans have significant advantages 
we own the night with our military force said merritt 
all our tanks and aircraft are night fighters we might be so 
effective so quickly that we can destroy their morale and keep our 
casualties down in the main and on the average were 
technologically far superior and our training is far superior 
he added that theres much talk about saddams 
