<TEXT>
when capt francisco mena deserted 
the army and joined el salvadors guerrillas they greeted him with 
tentative embraces hard stares and skepticism 
for a year a veteran fighter known as fredy never let mena walk 
behind him 
there was a ceremony that was a bit awkward mena who 
changed sides in 1981 told an interviewer i gave a talk and 
afterward the guerrillas began asking questions 
some of those questions he said were why did you stay so 
long in the army how many operations did you take part in how 
many of us have you killed 
damn i thought what have i gotten myself into here i 
came to help these guys and theyre busting my chops mena 
said 
he smiled at the recollection and brushed one hand through his 
wavy black hair the 47yearold rebel commander was in the 
delegation that on aug 22 ended a fruitless round of peace talks 
here with the government of alfredo cristiani the salvadoran 
president 
a nearly 11yearold civil war between the leftist farabundo 
marti national liberation front and a succession of usbacked 
governments has killed an estimated 72000 people most of them 
civilians 
the trip to costa rica was menas first involvement in the 
monthly negotiations and his first respite from the fighting in 
years 
he was included because the exclusive subject of the talks this 
month was a rebel demand that the armed forces be purged of corrupt 
officers and reformed that issue is the main sticking point in the 
negotations 
col mauricio vargas as a member of the government delegation 
protects the militarys interests at the talks 
officially the salvadoran military holds mena in contempt in 
the words of col orlando zepeda vice minister of defense that 
traitor and murderer has no moral right to make accusations or 
demands on us 
classmates at the military and some other officers however 
have demonstrated a camaraderie with mena that could help promote 
eventual accord 
lt col mauricio duke shook hands and chatted amiably with 
mena his former superior when they met in the lobby of the hotel 
where the talks were held 
mena gave a copy of his book from the national army to the 
guerrilla army to duke who responded with a sly smile 
gracias my captain 
the copy like another sent to vargas was inscribed lets 
not forget the 15th of october 
that is the date in 1979 when young officers vargas mena and 
duke included overthrew the rightist dictatorship of gen carlos 
humberto romero 
a broadbased government whose objective was national 
reconciliation resulted but a purge of the military old guard 
faltered repression and death squads followed and the result was 
civil war 
mena traces his change of heart to a year as an officer of the 
national guard a militarized police force 
he described counterinsurgency tactics that included torture 
rape and murder of alleged leftists and told of an initiation rite 
during which he declined an invitation to drive a bayonet through 
the heart of a suspect 
while he pondered such brutality later in his airconditioned 
office mena said the suspect and 11 others were killed in the 
gymnasium of the national guard headquarters 
that kind of thing consolidated my change of thinking by 
making me profoundly question the role we military men were 
playing he said it became denigrating for me to wear the 
national guard insignia 
the proclamation issued by those who carried out the 1979 coup 
promised respect for human rights an end to corruption and 
modernization of a semifeudal economy that left most salvadorans 
destitute 
peace is possible if military authorities honor those goals 
mena said but added the picture is this were getting nowhere 
in negotiations so lets have at it with the irons 
fredy the guerrilla fighter so wary of mena was killed in 
combat in 1985 
just before he died mena said they had a conversation in which 
fredy told him 
in those early days i didnt trust you a bit like you were 
still the enemy who ever would have believed that wed come to be 
like brothers that id gladly give my life for you 
