alan cranston dcalif who also asked mci and sprint to provide 
similar services to the troops 
if were using 20th century weapons we also should be using 
20th century communications cranston said in a statement he 
said a facsimile service would provide a big boost to morale for 
us forces participating in operation desert shield 
atampt said the duration of desert fax will depend on several 
factors including cost volume of messages and benefits to 
military personnel and their families 
