iraq has successfully tested an 
intermediaterange ballistic missile loaded with chemical weapons 
a newspaper reported today 
during the test last year iraq fired a missile loaded with a 
chemical warfare agent the los angeles times said quoting arab 
and us officials it did not identify by name 
the test in northwestern iraq shows that the government of 
saddam hussein can carry out a chemical weapons attack using 
missiles with a range of 175 to nearly 600 miles the newspaper 
said 
such missiles could reach us forces deployed in saudi arabia 
no country has ever launched a missile attack with chemical 
weapons iraq combined the two after its war with iran ended in 
1988 
officials say such an attack would be far more difficult for 
iraq than waging chemical war with conventional aircraft 
it is an extremely complicated and difficult operation said 
geoffrey kemp a former national security council staff member 
it requires that you have a mechanism that releases the gas at 
the right altitude as the missile is reentering the atmosphere 
because missiles can travel farther and faster than aircraft and 
are more difficult to intercept the test is seen as a serious 
threat 
in response the united states has deployed patriot 
surfacetoair missiles to intercept iraqi missiles the newspaper 
said the us plan is to intercept the missiles at high altitude 
and disperse the gas before it reaches the ground it said 
three types of iraqi missiles are soviet made and described by a 
us air force official as inaccurate 
they could be useful against an area target but not against a 
highvalue military target he said 
highvalue military targets include radar installations and air 
fields an area target is a population center 
iraq used chemical warfare extensively in the eightyear war 
with iran and experts say that contributed to irans acceptance of 
a united nations settlement in 1988 officials say american troops 
are well trained in chemical warfare 
