<TEXT>
a un committee today allowed india to 
send food to its citizens trapped by iraqs invasion of kuwait the 
vote came hours after the security council set strict guidelines 
for exceptions to the trade embargo 
let us be frank there is food in iraq and kuwait but the 
iraqi authorities have chosen to deprive the most vulnerable 
elements of the civilian society pushing them to the brink of 
starvation us ambassdor thomas pickering said 
the security council voted 132 late thursday to allow food 
shipments to iraq or occupied kuwait only to relieve human 
suffering and said humanitarian organizations must distribute the 
aid 
the councils committee on sanctions met later and gave india 
permission to send a shipload of food to its 140000 citizens in 
iraq and occupied kuwait 
in line with the resolution just adopted the sanctions 
committee has approved the sailing of a ship from india to kuwait 
to assist indian and other nationals in kuwait and iraq pickering 
said 
under the un embargo passed four days after iraqs aug 2 
invasion of kuwait only medical supplies or in humanitarian 
circumstances foodstuffs may be sent to iraq or kuwait 
india and the philippines had appealed to the security councils 
sanctions committee for permission to send food to their people 
still stranded in iraq and kuwait 
