<TEXT>
comedy actress athene seyler whose stage movie 
and radio career spanned most of this century has died her family 
reported she was 101 
she died at her home in london on wednesday her family said 
they did not give details on funeral arrangements 
said by one theater critic to resemble an irritable 
hippopotamus on stage she was recognized in the acting 
profession as one of the great technical experts on high comedy 
she specialized in playing quirky queens and crusty dowagers 
with plummy voices and quivering chins she especially favored the 
plays of william congreve oscar wilde william wycherley and 
richard sheridan 
critic james agate once said that when it came to comedy she 
could act any other english actress off the stage 
her plain looks generally ruled out romantic roles but combined 
with her sharp intelligence and vitality proved a considerable 
comic asset 
in later life she was mockingly critical of playwrights and 
directors alike 
of harold pinters 1975 play no mans land she remarked 
i couldnt follow a word of it when one of the characters 
yawned i said oh i do so agree rather too loudly and people in 
the audience turned and stared at me 
she made her london stage debut in 1909 but it was not until 
1920 when she played rosalind in shakespeares as you like it 
that her special talent for high comedy first showed 
she appeared in almost 20 movies including quiet wedding in 
1940 dear octopus in 1943 nicholas nickleby in 1947 and 
pickwick papers in 1952 
her last major stage appearance was in 1966 at the age of 77 in 
a memorable revival of the comedy arsenic and old lace in which 
she costarred with dame sybil thorndike she continued working on 
radio until she was well into her late 80s 
her first husband was newspaper editor james bury 
sterndalebennett by whom she had a daughter her second husband 
actor nicholas hannen died in 1972 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

