apparently started in a campground on the north fork of the 
tuolumne river within the stanislaus national forest west of 
yosemite national park the area is about 150 miles east of san 
francisco 
since there was no lightning in the area it is presumed the 
fire was caused by people the forestry department said 
officials said they are using over 100 engines seven air 
