the state attorney generals office has been looking for blan 
stewart 47 since halloween night 1988 when his airplane 
disappeared near lake martin in central alabama 
stewart who lived in huntsville had radioed that he was having 
engine trouble repeated searches of the lake by law enforcement 
officers and by firms hired by stewarts family and insurance 
companies never turned up the plane or a body 
on tuesday the fbi issued a fugitive warrant for stewart and 
joined the search agent tom wiseman said in an affidavit used to 
obtain the warrant the fbi quoted two unidentified sources 
including one huntsville resident who said they saw stewart in the 
virgin islands in late november or early december 1989 
the fbi said telephone records subpoenaed by the state attorney 
generals office showed a collect call from the virgin islands to 
stewarts wifes home in huntsville in march the call came six 
weeks before sarah robin stewart went to court to have her 
husband declared dead so she could collect on 4 million in life 
insurance a judge ruled however there was insufficient evidence 
to declare stewart dead 
the fbis affidavit said a third source who lives in huntsville 
