in a statement the pentagon said the 41400ton tanker was 
reported to have no cargo aboard 
after several requests to permit boarding the brewton fired 
the first warning shots from one of its 50caliber machine guns 
the pentagon said the darwin fired a second set of warning 
shots also from a 50caliber machine gun about 10 minutes 
later 
the tankers master then announced he would stop the ship and 
permit the boarding the pentagon said 
a joint boarding party boarded the tanker conducted a 
coordinated investigation and determined that the ship contained no 
prohibited cargo the pentagon statement said 
the first shots in the interdiction effort were fired aug 18 
when us navy ships attempted to halt two iraqi tankers neither 
ship was boarded 
the us forces now joined by the naval forces of several 
other nations are in the persian gulf region to enforce the 
unimposed economic sanctions in the hope of forcing iraq to 
withdraw from kuwait 
