deliveries are behind schedule however and there are only 51 new 
buses said metro spokesman dan williams 
the fivestation tunnel opens to the public saturday 
the mostly northsouth route stops at westlake mall stations in 
the financial district and historic pioneer square and surfaces at 
the international district near the kingdome sports center 
commuter frustration is high in the seattle area which 
experienced explosive suburban growth in the past decade the city 
has no lightrail system though the tunnel is equipped with 
recessed rails 
about 225000 people use metros buses daily and 84 percent of 
them travel to downtown seattle williams said 
the tunnel lies in the downtown freebus zone instituted years 
ago to ease traffic commuters from outside the city center must 
pay fares that begin at 75 cents 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

