stock prices declined broadly today as the 
market absorbed new signs of steppedup inflation and weak consumer 
spending 
the dow jones average of 30 industrials dropped 1114 to 
257153 in the first half hour of trading 
losers outnumbered gainers by more than 7 to 2 in nationwide 
trading of new york stock exchangelisted issues with 199 up 745 
down and 429 unchanged 
volume on the big board came to 1902 million shares as of 10 
am on wall street 
the labor department reported this morning that the producer 
price index of finished goods jumped 13 percent in august mostly 
because of sharp rises in energy prices separately the commerce 
department said retail sales dropped 06 percent 
neither of those figures came as a drastic surprise to wall 
street analysts who have been busy since midsummer trying to 
estimate the possible fallout from the showdown in the middle east 
and a doubling of world oil prices 
nevertheless analysts said the data served to reinforce fears 
of stagflation a combination of sluggish growth and increased 
inflationary pressures 
in that kind of climate few market participants can see much 
reason for optimism about the outlook for corporate profits and 
dividends 
