<TEXT>
investors eager to do their futures and options 
trading at night will have to wait a little longer 
partners in globex a proposed 24hour electronic system for 
trading financial futures and options said thursday they have 
pushed back the planned startup date from november to the first 
quarter of 1991 
the latest obstacle involves modifications to accommodate 
products offered by the chicago board of trade according to a 
statement issued jointly by the board of trade the chicago 
mercantile exchange and reuters holdings plc a british company 
that is supplying technology for the system 
the board of trade joined the venture in may after abandoning 
plans to develop a competing system 
the parties also have yet to iron out a firm agreement on 
sharing the operation of the system which is subject to approval 
by the board of trades directors and members according to the 
twoparagraph statement 
when the merc and reuters announced their globex plans in 
september 1987 they projected a launch date in the first quarter 
of 1989 
the parties said they have been pleased with the results of 
testing globexs functions 
globex would operate during the hours that the exchanges 
trading floors are closed 
it would theoretically enable participating brokers around the 
world to get orders filled at any time either through the 
traditional openoutcry method when the trading floors are open or 
through blind ordermatching by the globex computer when the floors 
are closed 
