<TEXT>
a virtual news blackout on national contract 
negotiations between the united auto workers union and general 
motors corp continued as bargainers faced a contract expiration 
tonight 
bargaining resumed this morning company and union officials 
said there was no allnight session thursday 
there was speculation thursday night that the silence indicated 
negotiators were making slow but steady progress toward a new 
threeyear agreement covering more than 300000 workers at the 
worlds largest automaker the current pact expires at midnight 
major issues yet to be resolved included job security wages and 
pensions according to a uaw official who declined to be 
identified tentative agreements have been reached on a variety of 
mostly noneconomic issues including health and safety and 
attendance policy 
the detroit free press reported in todays edition that gm and 
the union have agreed tentatively to a contract provision involving 
uaw leaders in decisions about where auto components or entire 
vehicles are made 
the newspaper quoting unidentified union officials said there 
were no references to specific goals for increasing the use of gm 
facilities and uaw workers in manufacturing parts for the huge 
automaker 
the sourcing issue has been emotional for uaw members who 
have complained the company has turned its back on unionized 
american workers in favor of nonunion sometimes overseas 
factories 
uaw vice president stephen yokich head of the unions 
bargaining effort with gm made a brief appearance thursday night 
in a hallway of the gm building where the negotiators are working 
he was dogged by reporters and television camera crews 
he declined to say anything about the talks 
everybody is curious dave perdue president of uaw local 
276 at gms arlington texas assembly plant said thursday 
theyre hungry for information 
the lack of information the lack of strike rhetoric that 
tells me i should anticipate a settlement 
in addition to the national contract more than 100 gmuaw local 
contracts covering specific working conditions on a plantbyplant 
basis remained unresolved thursday 
those contracts also expire at midnight as do uaw contracts 
with ford motor co and chrysler corp 
but the ford and chrysler talks have been put on hold pending 
the outcome of negotiations between the union and gm in all more 
than 450000 active workers are covered by the three contracts 
