<TEXT>
arizona public service co following up on a 
midyear announcement that it hoped to cut capital expenditures and 
trim its budget says it will eliminate 675 fulltime positions 
aps president mark de michele said thursday that one goal for 
the states largest utility was to reduce our pending 
rateincrease request before the arizona corporation commission and 
work toward a period of price stability 
de michele said he could not provide specifics on the size of 
the reduction 
aps executives said the cuts are needed to keep rates at a 
reasonable level and match competition in the utility industry 
in january aps filed a 271 million rate proposal seeking 
increases of 68 percent in 1991 1992 and 1993 the request has 
been amended to 65 percent per year or 259 million 
a sluggish economy that has resulted in a slowdown of customer 
growth also is a major factor in the costcutting effort the 
utility has roughly 591000 residential and commercial customers 
this is the third time aps has eliminated positions to try to 
cut costs it has cut 1548 jobs since 1988 generating 63 million 
in savings 
de michele said that in addition to the 13 percent cut in the 
companys fulltime nonnuclear workforce of 4908 aps will 
eliminate another 450 jobs by not filling vacant positions 
the targeted jobs include those of 300 unionized employees 315 
clericalprofessional positions and about 60 managers and 
supervisors they do not include about 400 jobs eliminated since 
jan 1 when the company had nearly 5800 fulltime employees and 
decided to adopt an earlyretirement program 
the reductions do not affect either employees or contract 
workers at the palo verde nuclear generating station the only 
nuclear facility in the state said aps spokesman wayne kaplan 
about 2840 people are on the palo verde workforce kaplan said 
the statement withheld details of the companys revised filing 
and stability plans and said the reorganization would take until 
the end of the year to complete 
under the plan employees holding jobs targeted for elimination 
first will be offered positions within the company a voluntary 
severance plan will follow layoffs then will go into effect aps 
executives said 
