<TEXT>
opec marked its 30th anniversary friday 
with its top official predicting the oilproducing organization 
would survive the persian gulf crisis that has badly tarnished its 
image 
a world without opec is unthinkable for as long as oil 
continues to provide the prime source of energy said subroto 
secretarygeneral of the 13nation organization of petroleum 
exporting countries 
opec will stay around we have survived crises before 
surely well survive this also all disputes ultimately get 
resolved he said in an anniversary message carried by the 
groups opecna news agency 
opec was created by saudi arabia venezuela iran iraq and 
kuwait on sept 14 1960 in baghdad iraq in an effort to give 
them more muscle to push up crude prices it has since grown to 13 
nations 
throughout its history the cartel has had to deal with a string 
of crises including iraqs 1980 invasion of neighbor iran 
this time the oil producer moved against another neighbor 
occupying tiny kuwait and creating more turmoil for the cartel 
in his statement subroto said the groups objectives remain 
sound they include coordinating oil policies of member nations 
steadying the world market ensuring a constant flow of oil 
revenues to members and maintaining an adequate supply of crude for 
consumers 
everyone is for a stable oil market he said no one wants 
violent fluctuations in prices 
he said the producing nations do not want a repeat of the 1980s 
when prices went on a rollercoaster ride that carried them to 
almost 40 a barrel before plunging to a little more than 10 
since iraqs invasion of kuwait on aug 2 crude prices have 
soared light sweet crude the benchmark american grade has been 
trading at about 31 a barrel 
a basket of crudes monitored by opec surged last week to 2884 
a barrel well above its target price of 21 dollars that was set 
shortly before the iraqi strike 
subroto who previously was indonesias oil minister said the 
cartel was in a position to meet the crude requirements of 
consuming nations well into the next century 
no one should think otherwise because of the temporary 
difficulties we face today he said 
opec president sadek boussena who is the algerian oil minister 
said producers and consumers can learn from the groups experience 
that what is needed is good will not ill will trust not 
suspicion and cooperation not confrontation 
in addition to the five founding members the group includes 
qatar indonesia libya the united arab emirates algeria 
nigeria ecuador and gabon 
