<TEXT>
here are thumbnail sketches of the top four 
management and labor leaders involved in national contract 
negotiations between general motors corp and the united auto 
workers union 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name robert stempel 
position chairman and chief executive officer 
age 57 
background stempel took over the worlds largest corporation on 
aug 1 and is gms first engineertrained chairman he joined the 
automakers oldsmobile division in 1958 and held various design and 
engineering positions in that division until 1973 when he was 
appointed special assistant to gm president edward n cole 
the following year he moved to the chevrolet division where he 
served in a variety of engineering divisions after a twoyear 
stint in gms pontiac division stempel headed overseas where he 
was appointed managing director of adam opel ag of west germany in 
1980 he returned to the united states as chevrolets general 
manager in 1982 
he was promoted to head the buickoldsmobile cadillac group 
before becoming an executive vice president in 1986 the following 
year he became gms 17th president a post he held until he 
succeeded retired gm chairman roger b smith 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name alfred s warren jr 
position vice president of industrial relations 
age 64 
background warren born in aliquippa pa took his current 
position on sept 1 1980 and is the veteran among this years top 
negotiators he joined gm in 1959 as assistant personnel director 
at chevrolets tonawanda engine plant in buffalo ny and was 
promoted to several plant manager positions he was transferred to 
the companys personnel administration staff in october 1973 
warren is a champion of joint companyunion programs and worked 
closely with retired uaw vice president donald ephlin in 
implementing a variety of joint programs in gm 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name owen bieber 
position president 
age 60 
background bieber a native of north dorr mich joined the 
uaw in 1948 while working at mcinerney spring and wire co in grand 
rapids mich he rose through the ranks through local 687 before 
being appointed to the international unions staff in 1961 
he served as an assistant director and director in region 1d in 
southwest lower michigan he was elected as a uaw vice president in 
1980 and was appointed head of the unions gm department a post he 
held before being elected president of the one millionmember union 
in 1983 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name stephen p yokich 
position vice president and director of the uaw gm department 
age 54 
background yokich whose grandfathers were active in uaw 
matters began working as a toolanddie maker in oak park mich 
his first union job was shop chairman in uaw local 155 he was 
appointed to the uaw staff by former union president walter 
reuther he held a series of international union offices including 
vice president of the agricultural implement department and the 
ford department before being named to his current position in june 
1989 
yokich is regarded as a tough negotiator and a likely successor 
to uaw president owen bieber 
