<TEXT>
the dutch electronics giant nv 
philips refused to comment friday on a report that it was pulling 
out of a multimilliondollar telecommunications project with atampt 
het financieele dagblad an authoritative dutch business 
newspaper said philips is planning to sell its 15 percent stake in 
atampt network systems international which develops and manufactures 
public telephone exchanges 
a philips spokesman refused to comment on the report saying the 
company would make an announcement only if and when it saw fit an 
american telephone amp telegraph co spokesman in the united states 
tom harris also said he had no comment on the report 
the newspaper added that philips would limit itself after the 
pullout to making only industrial telecommunications equipment 
including corporate switchboards 
philips share in the project with atampt was estimated by the 
newspaper at 100 million that would place the total worth of the 
joint venture at 666 million 
the report said atampt would absorb 9 percent of philips share 
while 6 percent would be taken over by telefonica sa a spanish 
telecommunications company 
but harris the atampt spokesman said that report was incorrect 
though telefonica announced friday it was buying a 6 percent stake 
in atampt network systems international he said that stake came out 
of atampts share in the venture 
after the telefonica transaction atampt will own 59 percent of 
the venture down from 65 percent harris said 
italys statecontrolled stet owns the other 15 percent 
atampt nsi the us companys main european operation produces 
software and hardware products for most of europes public 
telecommunications networks 
at a special shareholders meeting in july philips announced it 
was beginning a major restructuring to streamline its operations 
the announcement followed unexpectedly low firstquarter profit 
of 34 million down from 126 million in the first quarter last 
year 
philips president jan timmer warned at the meeting to expect 
more than 1 billion in losses and up to 10000 layoffs 
timmer was appointed last may in a widely publicized boardroom 
reshuffle and is reputed to be a ruthless costcutter 
philips which began as a small light bulb factory has grown to 
be one of the worlds biggest manufacturers of consumer 
electronics computers and other appliances but has been facing 
fierce competition from japanese companies 
meanwhile friday telefonica said it had reached an agreement to 
take the 6 percent stake in atampt nsi in exchange for its 20 percent 
share in a spanish microchip company 
in a joint statement statecontrolled telefonica said it was 
swapping its 20 percent share in atampt microelectronica sa for the 
stake in netherlandsbased atampt nsi 
atampt nsi will now own 100 percent of atampt microelectronica 
which in 1985 built a 200 million custom microchip factory just 
north of madrid 
telefonica president candido velazquez called the accord an 
important step in the growing process of internationalization of 
telefonica permitting us to directly participate in a european 
project like att nsi 
atampt president robert allen said the agreement permits us to 
widen our european perspectives and strengthen our position as a 
global company 
earlier friday atampt network systems espana presented a new 
100 million factory which will provide 250000 telephone lines to 
telefonica through 1990 and 300000 lines in 1991 
